  "description": "Solomon's two-ring architecture with strandTune at 7.02 semitones — Ring A carries the root, Ring B carries the fifth. The strong intra-ring coupling (0.8) gives each ring a built-in phase coherence, while the cross-ring coupling (0.3) creates a subtle gravitational pull between root and fifth. In legato mode, the glide carries both rings simultaneously through frequency space: the brief topological portamento of two braided power chords sliding together. macroKnot=0.22 bleeds gentle Trefoil asymmetry into Ring A — the root acquires a slight directional character, a lean into the melody.",
